tuples = (1,2,3)
print(tuples)
# this is a tuple in Python. Tuples are ordered collections of elements that can hold different data types. They are defined using parentheses () and can contain any number of elements.


tuples = (1,2,3)
tuples[0] = 5
print(tuples)
# here you cant change the value of a tuple because tuples are immutable in Python. Once a tuple is created, its elements cannot be modified. If you need a mutable collection, you can use a list instead.

